  "chapter": {
    "number": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Case against Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Hear now what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Arise, plead your case before the mountains,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and let the hills hear your voice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear, O mountains, the LORD’s indictment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you enduring foundations of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the LORD has a case against His people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will argue it against Israel:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "‘My people, what have I done to you?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Testify against Me how I have wearied you!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I brought you up from the land of Egypt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and redeemed you from the house of slavery.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I sent Moses before you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as well as Aaron and Miriam.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My people, remember what Balak king of Moab counseled",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and what Balaam son of Beor answered.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Remember your journey from Shittim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3824
          },
          {
            "text": "to Gilgal,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you may acknowledge the righteousness of the LORD.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "With what shall I come before the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when I bow before the God on high?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Should I come to Him with burnt offerings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with year-old calves?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would the LORD be pleased with thousands of rams,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with ten thousand rivers of oil?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Shall I present my firstborn for my transgression,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fruit of my body for the sin of my soul?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has shown you, O man, what is good.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "And what does the LORD require of you",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but to act justly, to love mercy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to walk humbly with your God?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Punishment of Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The voice of the LORD calls out to the city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "(and it is sound wisdom to fear Your name):",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Heed the rod",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the One who ordained it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can I forget any longer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O house of the wicked,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the treasures of wickedness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the short ephah, which is accursed?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can I excuse dishonest scales",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or bags of false weights?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the wealthy of the city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are full of violence,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and its residents speak lies;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their tongues are deceitful in their mouths.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I am striking you severely,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to ruin you because of your sins.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will eat but not be satisfied,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your hunger will remain with you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "What you acquire, you will not preserve;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and what you save, I will give to the sword.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will sow but not reap;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will press olives but not anoint yourselves with oil;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will tread grapes but not drink the wine.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have kept the statutes of Omri",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all the practices of Ahab’s house;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you have followed their counsel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will make you a desolation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your inhabitants an object of contempt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will bear the scorn of the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3825
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
